description:
Teaching work (known as specified work), as an activity, is regulated by law through the Education (Specified Work) (England) Regulations 2012/762. Regulation 5 lists the activities which are classed as specified work for the purposes of teaching in a school maintained by a local authority - which includes a maintained nursery - and a special school not so maintained:
 planning and preparing lessons and courses for pupils;
delivering lessons to pupils;
assessing the development, progress and attainment of pupils; and
 reporting on the development, progress and attainment of pupils.
